    "creation_date" : 1513274254,
    "answer_id" : 47819454,
    "question_id" : 47796757,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>At long last we found a solution that works for us and provides syntax highlighting and code completion for the Jenkinsfile present in an otherwise normal Java project in Idea.\nThe solution is taken from <a href=\"https://st-g.de/2016/08/jenkins-pipeline-autocompletion-in-intellij\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>, <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/48326267/1614555\">here</a> (and from additional personal experiments / research)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download the Groovy SDK (if you did not do so already) from <a href=\"http://groovy-lang.org/download.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">the Groovy Page</a> and configure it on your Java project. For help on this see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/46125537/1614555\">here</a></li>\n<li>Download the pipeline GDSL file from your Jenkins instance which should be available under a link like <a href=\"https://yourJenkinsInstance.tld/pipeline-syntax/gdsl\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://yourJenkinsInstance.tld/pipeline-syntax/gdsl</a>, and add it to the classpath of your Java project. E.g. by creating a new folder src/main/jenkins, putting the pipeline GDSL file there and marking the folder as source root in IntelliJ IDEA. <strong>Make sure that the file extension is <code>.gdsl</code>, not <code>.groovy</code>.</strong> Otherwise, code completion will not work.</li>\n<li>Add &quot;Jenkinsfile&quot; as a valid file name pattern for groovy files as described <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/48326267/1614555\">here</a></li>\n<li>To avoid the error message <code>'node' cannot be applied to '(groovy.lang.Closure&lt;java.lang.Object&gt;)</code>, you can add this line at the top of your Jenkinsfile:\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>// noinspection GroovyAssignabilityCheck\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7268572,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 5542443,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-xh1fR8zNDqY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAALY/n4hQ5NnM4Bo/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Neil Millard",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5542443/neil-millard"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1610716218,
    "last_edit_date" : 1610716218,
    "creation_date" : 1516177348,
    "answer_id" : 48296523,
    "question_id" : 47796757,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Looking at the source code, it looks like <code>COMMENTS</code> are not defined (they are commented out in the code)</p>\n<p>The <code>STEP_KEY</code> is defined as: <code>STEP_NAME=&quot;sh&quot; | &quot;parallel&quot;</code></p>\n<p>I'm not sure the plugin does much more and it hasn't been updated in 2 years.</p>\n"
  }, {
