    "question_id" : 47796757,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Jenkinsfile is a groovy like script, but normally IntelliJ map it to <em>TextMate</em> editor.</p>\n<p>To do that go to the settings menu, open the &quot;Editor&quot; item and then &quot;File Types&quot;. Now select &quot;TextMate&quot; in the upper list and add &quot;Jenkinsfile&quot;. You can also use a regex like &quot;Jenkinsfile*&quot; if you want to be more flexible regarding an optional file ending for the Jenkinsfile.</p>\n"
  } ],
